BARD QUICK START

This is the practical path for a new Bard.

1. Check yourself.

   bscore
   bmon on
   bcmds

   bscore shows your Bard state. bmon keeps important Bard updates visible.
   bcmds shows what you can use now and what unlocks later.

2. Fix your lute.

   fix lute

   Your guild lute is your fallback instrument. If it is missing or damaged,
   this restores it without needing to return to Adaon.

3. Learn your first combat song.

   pulsebeat

   Pulsebeat March is your first song field. It follows you, pulses while it
   lasts, helps nearby allies, and teaches you the rhythm of the Bard system.

4. Watch Performance.

   Performance is Bard momentum. It rises when you keep songs moving, especially
   when you vary forms instead of repeating the same thing. Charisma improves
   that momentum, makes songs stronger, and helps song fields linger. Stronger
   Bard powers and Finales care about Performance. Song forms have separate
   cooldowns, so pulsebeat into emberaria into echochord feels much faster than
   repeating the same song form.

5. Practice simple music.

   play lute <note>
   bardhelp songs

   Simple note practice is separate from battle songs. It is useful for flavor,
   roleplay, and learning note names. Battle songs are full commands such as
   pulsebeat, emberaria, echochord, and dirgeash.

6. Earn and explore.

   perform
   legend <item>
   lore <monster>

   Bards are social explorers. perform can earn coins, legend reads objects,
   and lore helps you judge creatures.

7. Build your Bard legend.

   gscore Bard
   bscore
   glevel

   Bards earn Bard XP by contributing to level-appropriate battles. Bard XP
   advances your guild level automatically when your character level, total
   guild levels, and Charisma allow it. Excess Bard XP remains banked until a
   blocked level becomes available. The glevel command at a Bard hall explains
   any current gate; it no longer spends ordinary character experience.

8. Buy instruments when you can.

   Alternate instruments are sold in the Bard Shoppe in the Darkwind Bard
   guildhall. Use instrument to choose one. Instruments change newer battle
   songs and unlock a few songs.

9. Choose an archetype at guild level 10.

   specialize
   specialize <archetype>

   Archetypes are not just labels. They change momentum, field strength,
   instrument affinity, hidden harmonies, and message flavor.

